track_notes:
I climbed Fumat, twice in two days in April 2015. Fumat is an imposing tall finger of rock with a tunnel through the bottom of it carrying the MA-2210 road. I would rate this as an an easier climb than it looks from the bottom. 
Leave the road near a road sign to climb up a bank (short scramble, 3 steps) on to the path which takes you up to a stoned donkey zig-zag trail. The col is soon reached and then you climb steeply. Several small cairns to watch for.
 
You may park on the left 50m after leaving the tunnel (fits about 5 cars in) or continue if full to one of three other small parking places within the next 1 KM. One on a right hand bend takes about 5 cars.
track_title: You have a few parking options - see text

track_notes:
In the summer months, access to Cap Formentor is temporarily closed to private cars. 
Bus number 334 runs every half hour from Port de Pollena and from Alcudia to Cap Formentor. Payment is made easy inside the bus by (credit/EC) card. The track starts at the Cala Murta / Cala Figuera bus stop and goes through the tunnel. Due to the road closure, there are only many cyclists in the tunnel and buses every half hour. The rest of the track follows that of G4OBK.
track_title: Fumat from bus stop Cala Murta / Cala Figuera
